<paragraph blockId="15.[151,1436,222,463]" pageId="15" pageNumber="316">
This is a genus of six Afrotropical species, conspicuously spotted with orange and normally found in forests (
<taxonomicName authority="Fabricius" authorityName="Fabricius" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Pardaleodes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="316" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tibullus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="316">P. tibullus</emphasis>
(Fabricius)
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName box="[423,500,258,283]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Pardaleodes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="316" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bule">
<emphasis box="[423,500,258,283]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="316">P. bule</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<collectingCountry box="[508,600,258,283]" name="Netherlands" pageId="15" pageNumber="316">Holland</collectingCountry>
) or in disturbed forest and adjacent open areas. Five species of the genus have been reared from grasses, and probably all will be found to be grass-feeders. T.B. Larsen (pers. comm. 
<number box="[1371,1429,295,319]" pageId="15" pageNumber="316" value="2014.0">2014</number>
) reared 
<taxonomicName authority="Stoll" authorityName="Stoll" box="[228,409,330,355]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Pardaleodes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="316" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="edipus">
<emphasis box="[228,330,330,355]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="316">P. edipus</emphasis>
(Stoll)
</taxonomicName>
from at least two species of grass in Lagos in 
<number box="[937,996,330,355]" pageId="15" pageNumber="316" value="1969.0">1969</number>
. In 
<collectingCountry box="[1039,1193,330,355]" name="Ivory Coast" pageId="15" pageNumber="316">Côte d’Ivoire</collectingCountry>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Vuattoux" box="[1205,1390,331,355]" pageId="15" pageNumber="316" refString="Vuattoux, R. (1999) Les lepidopteres hesperiides de la Station de Lamto (Cote d'Ivoire). Lambillionea, 94, 562 - 568." type="journal article" year="1999">
Vuattoux (
<number box="[1324,1382,331,355]" pageId="15" pageNumber="316" value="1999.0">1999</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
has reared 
<emphasis box="[235,440,367,390]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="316">P. i n c er t a m u rci a</emphasis>
(Plötz) once from 
<taxonomicName box="[684,914,366,391]" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Imperata" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="15" pageNumber="316" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="cylindrica">
<emphasis box="[684,914,366,391]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="316">Imperata cylindrica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="Westwood" authorityName="Westwood" box="[984,1299,366,391]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Pardaleodes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="316" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="sator" subSpecies="sator">
<emphasis box="[984,1149,367,390]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="316">P. sator sator</emphasis>
(Westwood)
</taxonomicName>
once from 
<taxonomicName box="[151,386,402,427]" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Oplismenus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="15" pageNumber="316" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="hirtellus">
<emphasis box="[151,386,402,427]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="316">Oplismenus hirtellus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Both 
<taxonomicName box="[467,577,404,427]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Pardaleodes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="316" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="incerta">
<emphasis box="[467,577,404,427]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="316">P. incerta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<emphasis box="[637,721,404,427]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="316">P. s a t o r</emphasis>
occur as far east as western 
<collectingCountry box="[1065,1138,403,427]" name="Kenya" pageId="15" pageNumber="316">Kenya</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry box="[1198,1299,402,427]" name="Tanzania" pageId="15" pageNumber="316">Tanzania</collectingCountry>
in different subspecies (
<figureCitation box="[285,396,438,463]" captionStart="FIGURE 11" captionStartId="15.[151,250,1484,1506]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,518,1459]" captionTargetId="figure@15.[151,1436,518,1460]" captionTargetPageId="15" captionText="FIGURE 11. Adults of Pardaleodes spp., Kenya. 1, female P. incerta incerta sunbathing, Shimba Hills, 13 Dec 1990; 2, male P. incerta incerta at flower of Justicia flava, Kakamega Forest, 17 Jun 1991; 3, female P. sator pusiella (Mabille) sunbathing, Kakamega Forest, 17 Jun 1991; 4, P. sator pusiella at flower of Justicia flava, Kakamega Forest, 17 Jun 1991." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/251871/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="316">
Figure 
<number box="[367,396,439,463]" pageId="15" pageNumber="316" value="11.0">11</number>
</figureCitation>
), but we have not located the early stages of either.
</paragraph>
